1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
One Codex session fails.
A rule is added.

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:07,300
The next session fails the same way.
A Skill is added.

3
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:12,300
It fails again. Another safeguard is
added. The environment keeps growing.

4
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:14,800
Creation is not improvement.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:19,500
Metabolism reuses what works,
then revisits every intervention.

6
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,400
A session leaves evidence.

7
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Codex proposes the smallest change.
A human approves or rejects.

8
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:30,500
The next session returns evidence.
Now the loop is complete.

9
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:34,100
Useful paths brighten.
Unsupported branches fade.

10
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:39,700
GPT-5.6 reviewed six sessions,
not fourteen rollout files.

11
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:45,100
Eight forks and 210 duplicate
user turns inflated the evidence.

12
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:50,800
GPT-5.6 proposed one PATCH
and one NO CHANGE / REUSE.

13
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:54,600
The existing rule already covered
the repeated request.

14
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,800
So Codex reuses it instead of
creating another instruction.

15
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:03,300
Runtime bounds the evidence.
It makes zero semantic decisions.

16
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:09,100
GPT-5.6 groups intent and authors
the proposed intervention.

17
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:13,900
Runtime validates its evidence links
and exact artifact bytes.

18
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:18,100
It seals the reviewed proposal
inside an approval digest.

19
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:20,500
Change a single byte after review.

20
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:23,000
The deterministic gate rejects it.

21
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:27,100
Restore the reviewed bytes.
A human approves the proposal.

22
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:30,600
Apply keeps a receipt and
a reversible archive.

23
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:34,800
The later review returns to the
original success contract.

24
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:39,200
Expected effect on one side.
Withdrawal condition on the other.

25
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:43,900
The Agent can reinforce a useful path
or repair the intervention.

26
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:48,800
Or stage a retirement candidate when
withdrawal condition is met.

27
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:52,300
A human may archive it.
Rollback remains available.

28
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:56,400
This is not model training.
The collaboration layer adapts.

29
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,000
An Agent can add.

30
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:02,200
A healthy collaboration can also
let go.
